Plugging this Lagrangian into the Euler-Lagrange equation of motion for a field, we get: (ic\gamma^\mu D_\mu-mc^2)\psi=0 \partial_
u F^{
u\mu}=-ec ar\psi\gamma^\mu\psi The first equation is the Dirac equation in the electromagnetic field and the second equation is a set of Maxwell equations (\partial_
u F^{
u\mu}=-ej^\mu) with a source j^\mu=c ar\psi\gamma^\mu\psi, which is a 4-current comming from the Dirac equation.
